&lt;p&gt;Locum Consultant Anaesthetist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Locum Consultant Anaesthetist 6 month fixed term contract with the possibility of extension&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Previous applicants need not apply&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates are invited to apply for the above posts, working in our Critical Care and Anesthesia departments at Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust - University hospital Lewisham and Queen Elizabeth Hospital Woolwich.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a conscientious and diligent anesthetist who has a caring attitude to patients to join our team of 45 Anesthetists to provide elective and emergency care to our adult and paediatric patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post comprises 8.5 PA for direct clinical care and 1.5 supporting professional activity (SPA) appointments. We are looking for dedicated anesthetist’s committed to maintaining and developing the highest standard of care to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will need to have the ability to work in a multidisciplinary team evidence of ability to organise Rota’s and understand the principles of clinical audit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder would need to have experience of teaching basic skills to under graduates and the ability to teach clinical skills to trainees of all levels as well as provide evidence of participation in audit projects with specific relevance to subspecialty interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All candidates must be eligible for full GMC registration and either already be on the Specialist Register or be within six months of receiving CCST/ CCT. Essential qualifications for the post are MBBS or equivalent and FRCA or equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To arrange a visit or for further information about the post, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr George Mathew - Consultant Anaesthetist Clinical Director of Anaesthesia at UHL george.mathew1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chelsea Gordon, Associate Service Manager - ITU, Anesthetics and Pain – chelsea.gordon@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
